President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Roy A. Bernardi as a Governor of the United States Postal Service. Bernardi is currently a managing partner of The Bernardi Group, LLC, and has previous experience as a Senior Advisor for CohnReznick, LLP and Vice President of Government Relations for CGI Technologies and Solutions Inc. He also served as Deputy Secretary of the Department of Housing and Urban Development (HUD) during the administration of President George W. Bush. Additionally, President Trump announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key positions in his Administration, including Siri Terjesen, Max Miller, Michael S. Glassner, Adam Telle, Paul-Noel Chretien, Paul E. Dans, Anthony J. Tata, Bryan Lanza, Rev. Eve Nunez, and Antonio L. Medina Comas.